sp.p:
To pluck the Magic Branch from the holy tomb of St. Rosalie. That done, he is surely ours;
       for, possession of unchecked power will lead his heart to sin, and sin—leads unto
        us.

I got a little out of the way, behind a pillar, that I mightn't be killed by mistake, when,
       bounce! something flew by me, and in a moment, bounce! it flew back again with Duke Robert;
       and, oh, Alice, only guess who that something was.
